Pass\'e2\'80\'99d on, and sate by faithful Mentor\'e2\'80\'99s side;\
With Antiphus, and Halitherses sage\
(His father\'e2\'80\'99s counsellors, revered for age).\
Of his own fortunes, and Ulysses\'e2\'80\'99 fame,\
Much ask\'e2\'80\'99d the seniors; till Peiraeus came.\
The stranger-guest pursued him close behind;\
Whom when Telemachus beheld, he join\'e2\'80\'99d.\
He (when Peiraeus ask\'e2\'80\'99d for slaves to bring\
The gifts and treasures of the Spartan king)\
Thus thoughtful answer\'e2\'80\'99d: \'e2\'80\'9cThose we shall not move,\
