\
\'e2\'80\'9cUlysses late he saw, on Cretan ground\
(His fathers guest), for Minos\'e2\'80\'99 birth renown\'e2\'80\'99d.\
He now but waits the wind to waft him o\'e2\'80\'99er,\
With boundless treasure, from Thesprotia\'e2\'80\'99s shore.\'e2\'80\uc0\u157 \
\
To this the queen: \'e2\'80\'9cThe wanderer let me hear,\
