\'e2\'80\'9cHe only asks a more propitious hour,\
And shuns (who would not?) wicked men in power;\
At evening mild (meet season to confer)\
By turns to question, and by turns to hear.\'e2\'80\uc0\u157 \
\
\'e2\'80\'9cWhoe\'e2\'80\'99er this guest (the prudent queen replies)\
