She said, infusing courage with the word.\
Jove and Jove\'e2\'80\'99s daughter then the chief implored,\
And, whirling high, dismiss\'e2\'80\'99d the lance in air.\
Full at Eupithes drove the deathful spear:\
The brass-cheek\'e2\'80\'99d helmet opens to the wound;\
He falls, earth thunders, and his arms resound.\
Before the father and the conquering son\
Heaps rush on heaps, they fight, they drop, they run\
Now by the sword, and now the javelin, fall\
The rebel race, and death had swallow\'e2\'80\'99d all;\
But from on high the blue-eyed virgin cried;\
Her awful voice detain\'e2\'80\'99d the headlong tide:\
\'e2\'80\'9cForbear, ye nations, your mad hands forbear\
