But Jove\'e2\'80\'99s red arm the burning thunder aims:\
Before Minerva shot the livid flames;\
Blazing they fell, and at her feet expired;\
Then stopped the goddess, trembled and retired.\
\
\'e2\'80\'9cDescended from the gods! Ulysses, cease;\
Offend not Jove: obey, and give the peace.\'e2\'80\uc0\u157 \
